    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pairs of naturally curved timbers that rise from the ground or outer walls of buildings to support a ridge beam; joined at the top and connected by tie beams.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
